South Africa exploded in a celebration of tears, cheers and dancing as the Springboks dominated their English rivals to win the finals of the Rugby World Cup in Japan on Saturday. Ahead of the hotly contested final, fans, schools and even President Cyril Ramaphosa met with Boks rallied behind the national team to give them messages of support. The Boks went into the match as slight underdogs, but they were superb from start to finish as they dominated almost every department against an English outfit that could not repeat its heroic semi-final performance against the All Blacks. LIVE | Go Bokke! SA celebrates as Springboks win the Rugby World Cup WATCH | Bok fans galore in Dubai pub A sea of Bok supporters were spotted in a bar in Dubai, UAE to watch the Rugby World Cup final between the Springboks and England on Saturday. 